[1mNAME[0m
       info - readable online documentation

[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
       The  Info  file  format is an easily-parsable representation for online
       documents.  It can be read by [4memacs(1)[24m and  [4minfo(1)[24m  among  other  pro-
       grams.

       Info  files are usually created from [4mtexinfo(5)[24m sources by [4mmakeinfo(1)[24m,
       but can be created from scratch if so desired.

       For a full description of the Texinfo language  and  associated  tools,
       please  see  the  Texinfo  manual  (written  in  Texinfo itself).  Most
       likely, running this command from your shell:
              [4minfo[24m [4mtexinfo[24m
       or this key sequence from inside Emacs:
              [4mM-x[24m [4minfo[24m [4mRET[24m [4mm[24m [4mtexinfo[24m [4mRET[24m
       will get you there.
